<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="diagnosis">
<!--template match = paragraph[descendant::heading]--><!--template match = heading--><title>Diagnosis</title>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Recognized by a combination of genital characters. Male palp: tegular apophysis small, translucent, oriented distad, parallel to plane of bulb, laterally barb-shaped (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-10--189-232-1667-1693-">Figs 6E</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-11--189-232-1691-1717-">7E</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-12--189-232-1691-1717-">8E</xref>
). Tegulum presents single sinus shape curve of sperm duct (in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Evippa</tp:taxon-name>
: two) (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-10--189-232-1667-1693-">Fig. 6E</xref>
). Epigyne: rounded or hat-shaped, wider than long, septum wide. Atria narrow, shallow, greatly constricted distally (in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Evippa</tp:taxon-name>
: width approximately equal throughout), similar to epigyne of 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>E. squamulatum</tp:taxon-name>
, but proximal portion of atrium wide (in 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>E. squamulatum</tp:taxon-name>
proximal portion of atrium slit-shaped) (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-14--189-232-1893-1919-">Figs 10E</xref>
, 
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-17--188-231-1894-1920-">13B, D</xref>
). It is the only 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Evippinae</tp:taxon-name>
in 
Israel
covered in flat, leaf-shaped setae and without annulations on the legs.
</p>
</tp:treatment-sec>
